Russia’s RTS Stock-Index Futures Fall 0.1% at Start of Trading

-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 
2011-04-01T15:16:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-01/russia-s-rts-stock-index-futures-fall-0-1-at-start-of-trading.html
Russia ’s RTS stock-index futures
expiring in June fell 0.1 percent to 203,490 by 11:08 a.m. in
 New York .  Contracts on OAO Lukoil, the country’s second-biggest oil
producer, declined 0.1 percent.  OAO Sberbank, Russia’s largest
lender, was little changed, while contracts on OAO Gazprom, the
natural-gas export monopoly, gained 0.1 percent. The Market
Vectors Russia ETF, a U.S.-traded fund that holds Russian
shares, rose almost 2 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Halia Pavliva in New York at 
 hpavliva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
